This paper is primarily focused on evaluating the performance of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) on synthetic data distributions. As such, it is likely to fall under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, since GANs are commonly used in computer vision applications, Computer Vision (cs.CV) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of hyperparameters on GAN performance, which is a topic of interest in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity and size of the underlying distribution, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SD).
